      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 2026-05-10</p>

      <p>
        Lolipants (“we”, “us”) provides a fashion design and ordering experience.
        This policy explains what data we collect, why we collect it, and the
        choices you have.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account data</strong>: name, email, auth identifiers.</li>
        <li><strong>Design content</strong>: saved designs, text layers, images you upload for prints.</li>
        <li><strong>Order data</strong>: delivery address, city, phone, notes, order status history.</li>
        <li><strong>Device & app data</strong>: basic diagnostics needed to operate the service.</li>
        <li><strong>Push notification identifiers</strong>: a OneSignal player/device id if you enable notifications.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Camera and photos</h2>
      <p>
        The app may request camera access for measurement estimation and to
        capture images for design uploads. You can deny permission and still
        use most features.
      </p>

      <h2>How we use data</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To create and manage your account.</li>
        <li>To save designs and fulfill orders with tailors and couriers.</li>
        <li>To send transactional updates (e.g., order status) if you opt in.</li>
        <li>To maintain security, prevent abuse, and debug reliability issues.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Payments</h2>
      <p>
        Payments are processed by a payment provider. We do not store your full
        card details on our servers.
      </p>

      <h2>Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We share data only as needed to provide the service (for example, with
        tailors/couriers for delivery fulfillment, and with infrastructure
        providers for hosting and messaging).
      </p>

      <h2>Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We keep data as long as needed to provide the service and comply with
        legal obligations, then delete or anonymize it where possible.
      </p>

      <h2>Your choices</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Access and update your profile information.</li>
        <li>Disable push notifications in your device settings.</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your account by contacting support.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
